      <hedline>
        <hl1>Light a Bulb, Save Earth</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sam Montgomery letter says light cast by compact fluorescents may not be as pleasing as from incandescent bulbs, but it is better than damaging Earth further (Jan 7 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Incandescence, Yes. Fluorescence, We'll See'' (Week in Review, Jan. 7):</p>
        <p>We can all agree that the light cast by compact fluorescent light bulbs is not as pleasing as that of incandescent bulbs.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Incandescence, Yes. Fluorescence, We'll See'' (Week in Review, Jan. 7):</p>
        <p>We can all agree that the light cast by compact fluorescent light bulbs is not as pleasing as that of incandescent bulbs.</p>
        <p>Unfortunately, the aesthetics of deforestation, coastal erosion, drought, wildfires, shrinking glaciers, mosquito-borne diseases and species dying off is worse.</p>
        <p>Sam Montgomery  Los Angeles, Jan. 8, 2007</p>
      </block>
